#: src/rust-2024/static-mut-reference.md:1
msgid "Disallow references to static mut"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/static-mut-reference.md:3
msgid ""
"🚧 The 2024 Edition has not yet been released and hence this section is "
"still \"under construction\"."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/static-mut-reference.md:5
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/static-mut-reference.md:7
msgid ""
"The [`static_mut_refs`](../../rustc/lints/listing/warn-by-default."
"html#static-mut-refs) lint is now a hard error that cannot be disabled. This "
"prevents taking a shared or mutable reference to a `static mut`."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/static-mut-reference.md:12
msgid "Details"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/static-mut-reference.md:14
msgid ""
"Taking a reference to a [`static mut`](../../reference/items/static-items."
"html#mutable-statics) is no longer allowed:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/static-mut-reference.md:22
#: src/rust-2024/static-mut-reference.md:23
#: src/rust-2024/static-mut-reference.md:24
msgid "// ERROR: reference of mutable static\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/static-mut-reference.md:28
msgid ""
"Shared or mutable references of mutable static are almost always a mistake "
"and can lead to undefined behavior and various other problems in your code. "
"For example, another thread writing to the `static mut` will cause an "
"aliasing violation and incur [Undefined Behavior](../../reference/behavior-"
"considered-undefined.html)."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/static-mut-reference.md:36
msgid "Migration"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2024/static-mut-reference.md:38
msgid "🚧 The automatic migration for this has not yet been implemented."
msgstr ""
